<h2 id="risk-assessment">Risk Assessment</h2>
<p>Both options carry different risk profiles for borrowers.</p>
<h3 id="personal-loan-risks">Personal Loan Risks</h3>
<p><strong>Fixed Payment Obligation</strong>: You must pay the same amount monthly regardless of your financial situation.</p>
<p><strong>Credit Score Impact</strong>: Missing payments damages your credit rating and affects future borrowing ability.</p>
<p><strong>Debt Service Ratio</strong>: High loan payments reduce your ability to qualify for other credit facilities.</p>
<p><strong>Interest Rate Risk</strong>: Variable rate loans expose you to rising interest costs over time.</p>
<h3 id="credit-card-risks">Credit Card Risks</h3>
<p><strong>Debt Spiral</strong>: Minimum payments can trap you in long-term debt cycles with mounting interest charges.</p>
<p><strong>Spending Temptation</strong>: Available credit may encourage unnecessary purchases and lifestyle inflation.</p>
<p><strong>Variable Interest Rates</strong>: Banks can increase rates with proper notice, raising your borrowing costs.</p>
<p><strong>Multiple Fee Exposure</strong>: Various charges can accumulate quickly if youâ€™re not careful with usage patterns.</p>
