<p><strong>Business Exception</strong>: Self-employed individuals may deduct interest if loans fund business operations.</p>
<p><strong>Documentation Required</strong>: Maintain clear records showing business use of loan proceeds.</p>
<h3 id="credit-card-tax-treatment">Credit Card Tax Treatment</h3>
<p><strong>Personal Use</strong>: Credit card interest and fees are not tax-deductible for personal expenses.</p>
<p><strong>Business Expenses</strong>: Companies can deduct credit card interest paid on business-related purchases.</p>
<p><strong>Mixed Use</strong>: Separate business and personal expenses to claim appropriate deductions.</p>
